2500|$|The User <b>Datagram</b> Protocol is a {{connectionless}} <b>datagram</b> protocol. Like IP, it is a best effort, [...] "unreliable" [...] protocol. Reliability {{is addressed}} through error detection using a weak checksum algorithm. UDP is typically used for {{applications such as}} streaming media (audio, video, Voice over IP etc.) where on-time arrival {{is more important than}} reliability, or for simple query/response applications like DNS lookups, where the overhead of setting up a reliable connection is disproportionately large. Real-time Transport Protocol (RTP) is a <b>datagram</b> protocol that is designed for real-time data such as streaming audio and video.|$|E
